<br>
Yet, something had entered the valley several years ago.  Something that made the amazons here suddenly dissappear.  With nothing left but a few huts, and thankfully a few scrolls.  Hippolyte glanced up into the mountains.  She would have to tell Celaneo of the scrolls she hid in a cave up there.  Perhaps, those scrolls might help.  Lalita might could find something in them that she would recognize as what happened.  <br>
<br>
Reaching the end of the road, Hippolyte had her mare slip thru the thick woods in a long weaving pattern.  Making sure not to follow anything that looked like a trail.  Then the thick brush parted to reveal the village.  Hippolyte smiled and urged the mare into a trot.  Then as the mare passed the first huts and buildings, she slid off it's back and began to walk it.  Her eyes dancing over the buildings that brought back memories. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#993300>(6/6/03 1:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.speedis.org/images/214.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Returning to her sister's home</span><hr size=1> Kalasin watched the amazon queen from a fair distance, far enough that it would take a good pair of eyes to spot her. After a moment the young woman decided that she would go and greet the Themisycrian queen. She quickly moved from where she had been hidden and towards the Queen. She knew there was no reason to draw her sword, Hippolyte would not do her harm.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yasoo Vasilissa Hippolyte.&quot; Kalasin said brightly. &quot;What brings you to the Crimson Valley?&quot;<br>
<br>
The pretty young amazon tossed her long blonde hair over her shoulder and smiled brilliantly at the Themisycrian Queen. Since having been in the Crimson Valey, Kalasin had become a much happier woman, and it was plain to see.<br>
