<br>
&quot;Actually, I have come to see how Celaneo is doing in and if I can help rebuild this ancient city in anyway,&quot; Hippolyte's brown eyes danced around the village with a slight smile.  &quot;This once was an incredible city, it would be nice to see it do the same once more.  Maybe it would bring my sister back...,&quot; Hippolyte got quiet.  She had no idea what had happened to Eponin...or Cel and the others for that matter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#993300>(6/9/03 2:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.speedis.org/images/214.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Returning to her sister's home</span><hr size=1> Kalasin nodded, eagerly taking in all that was said before she dared to reply. It was not easy for her to hold conversations in Greek, though her skill was considerably increasing by the day.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well,&quot; she indicated the city, &quot;I am sure there is something to do here, the place isn't exactly a holiday destination is it?&quot;<br>
<br>
She paused for a moment, thinking of something to say. &quot;I could take you to find Celaneo and Lalita if you would like?&quot;<br>
