alley sun seems to be shinning on you here, Kalasin.  Things are well with you then?!&quot;   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#993300>(6/10/03 9:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=52.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.speedis.org/images/214.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Returning to her sister's home</span><hr size=1> Kalasin nodded, smiling almost as brightly as the sun was shining. “If there was a word to describe how good I am feeling at the moment, it would be used.” She replied. “The Fates have been good to me.”<br>
She always felt slightly awkward referring to Greek deities in her common speech, she acknowledged that the Greek deities were gods, but preferred to steer clear of them. It seemed like a mutual agreement, because they kept clear of her too. As a general rule, the few Greek immortals that she had met had not liked her at all, and she the same. However, she was constantly among people that worshipped them, so perhaps speaking more like them was not a bad thing.<br>
“And yourself? Things have been well in Themisycra?”<br>
As she spoke the young woman gestured for the Amazon Queen to follow her.<br>
